1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,300
<i>You have to climb
Mount Kusama</i>

2
00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:04,867
<i> and you must do a ritual.</i>

3
00:00:04,867 --> 00:00:07,400
<i> - But you need a date.
- For your dad?</i>

4
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:08,733
<i> Does your mom know about that?</i>

5
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,567
<i>Not for my dad!
A date for you!</i>

6
00:00:11,567 --> 00:00:14,700
<i> Look! I don't need your help!</i>

7
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:17,233
<i>You are the most useless
family member!</i>

8
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,867
<i> Is there...
a private tour available?</i>

9
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:20,467
<i> - Sir Justin's does that.
- He said Sir Justin.</i>

10
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:22,333
<i> - Miss Cheska.
- Oh?</i>

11
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,833
<i>- She'll come with you, too.
- You're coming too, right?</i>

12
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>- Oh, I'd love to.
- Welcome to Hotel 88.</i>

13
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:29,533
<i>The hotel that will
force you to participate.</i>

14
00:00:29,533 --> 00:00:32,567
<i>You said you saw
a folder when Uncle Mike left.</i>

15
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:35,667
<i>Ah, yes. I just mentioned
it to Sir Henry recently.</i>

16
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:39,000
<i> But do you know what's in it?
Or who's it from?</i>

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,267
<i> The courier just gave it,
but I'm sure it's Sir Mike's.</i>

18
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,633
- [SCREAMS]<i> Ahh!
</i>- What happened?

19
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,233
<i> - What's that smell?
- That odor needs</i>

20
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:47,467
<i>to be eliminated
by tonight.</i>

21
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,800
<i>- Fine, I'll do it.
- [CLATTERS]</i>

22
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,767
[SCREAMS] Ah!

23
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,933
<i> Gio?</i>

24
00:00:56,233 --> 00:01:03,200
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,567
Here's the mouse.

26
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,533
Do you really have
to show it to me?

27
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,400
I didn't know
you were there.

28
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,900
Wait!
Where will you throw it?

29
00:01:25,967 --> 00:01:32,900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:27,400
Gio, where will you throw it?

31
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:31,300
No!

32
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,500
What do you
mean by "No"?

33
00:02:34,433 --> 00:02:37,000
They won't collect trash yet.
It'll stink there.

34
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:39,333
[CLICKS TONGUE] Tsk.

35
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:41,067
I told you
not to throw it there.

36
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:43,567
Throw it outside
the hotel premises.

37
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,800
You're still acting bossy
over this?

38
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,567
I think you forgot that I'm
still the GM here, Gio.

39
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,733
You're still supervising me
throwing the mouse?

40
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:52,833
- The mouse might escape!
- What?

41
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:55,433
What do you mean?
The mouse is dead!

42
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:56,633
What's going on with you?

43
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,600
Whatever, just throw it far away
for the hotel's safety.

44
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,867
- No!
- [CLICKS TONGUE] Tsk.

45
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:03,833
You've always had
that reaction about mice.

46
00:03:04,467 --> 00:03:11,467
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:17,000
- [LUNA]<i> Gio, there's a mouse!
</i>- A  mouse?!

48
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,967
<i>- Get it! Get it!
- [MOUSE SQUEAKS]</i>

49
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:21,900
<i> It's right there!
It's right there! Get it!</i>

50
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:23,733
<i> Hurry! Hurry!</i>

51
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:25,500
<i> Go slowly, slowly!</i>

52
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:29,033
[SCREAMS] Gio! It ran away!

53
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,867
<i> It ran... oh no, it got away!
It's under the bed!</i>

54
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:34,033
<i> - Where?
- It's under the bed!</i>

55
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:37,033
<i> Wait, wait.
You need to watch out for it.</i>

56
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,667
- [MOUSE SQUEAKS]
- [SCREAMS] Ah!

57
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,867
<i>There you go!
Did you catch it?</i>

58
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,733
<i> - Did you catch it?
- Should I take a look?</i>

59
00:03:44,733 --> 00:03:46,833
<i> - Don't look!
- How will I know?</i>

60
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:49,767
<i>It might escape!
You should knock.</i>

61
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:52,900
[MOUSE SQUEAKS]

62
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,100
<i> Slowly.</i>

63
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:56,567
[KNOCKS]

64
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:59,533
[MOUSE SQUEAKS]

65
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,600
- [KNOCKS]
- Hmm?

66
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:04,767
I think it's not moving anymore.

67
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:06,800
<i> Maybe it's just there.</i>

68
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,067
<i>- I think that's fine.
- Sure.</i>

69
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:12,567
[PANTING]

70
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:13,733
<i> I'm tired.</i>

71
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:17,200
[MOUSE SQUEAKS]

72
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:20,667
[SCREAMS] Ah!

73
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:22,533
<i>What's going on?!
You're so noisy!</i>

74
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:24,000
<i> What's wrong with you both?!</i>

75
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:27,600
<i> Grandma...</i>

76
00:04:27,633 --> 00:04:29,100
[LAUGHS]

77
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,733
<i> If this dead mouse
comes back...</i>

78
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:32,900
[PLASTIC RUSTLING]

79
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,700
<i> Hmm.</i>

80
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:40,067
<i> You know,
sometimes I think about</i>

81
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:42,167
<i> what I would do without you.</i>

82
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:44,633
<i> Who'll chase away
the mice in my life?</i>

83
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:46,500
[SCOFFS] Don't think about that.

84
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,133
<i>How could I not
think about that?</i>

85
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:50,067
<i>They keep popping
out of nowhere!</i>

86
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:51,700
<i> Because that won't happen.</i>

87
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:53,967
<i> Gio.</i>

88
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:56,233
<i>There are so many mice
in Manila.</i>

89
00:04:56,233 --> 00:05:03,200
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,533
<i>That won't happen
because I won't leave you.</i>

91
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:21,767
["TADHANA" BY
SOFRONIO VASQUEZ PLAYING]

92
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:43,800
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO
VASQUEZ CONTINUES]

93
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:53,600
[PLASTIC RUSTLING]

94
00:05:58,367 --> 00:06:01,200
[CHESKA] Hey, stop frowning.

95
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,233
There's a guest coming.

96
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:05,467
We'll just accompany
them, right?

97
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:08,000
My god... Justin please...

98
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:10,300
Keep in mind that you're still
one of the owners.

99
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:12,400
Trixie and I are
just siblings of the owners.

100
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,800
Stop acting like that.

101
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:17,233
I'm doing this so I won't
embarass Martin.

102
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:19,067
My God!

103
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:22,400
Let's just think of it as
us helping our siblings.

104
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:28,100
- Hey! Energy! Energy!
- Ah!

105
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,300
There's a guest!

106
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:31,267
How will we attract guests?

107
00:06:31,267 --> 00:06:33,400
Stand up! Jump around!
That's it! Smile!

108
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,833
[CHESKA] Energy!

109
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:38,000
What's up with your faces?
That's not exactly welcoming.

110
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,467
- Pull yourselves together.
- Let's go?

111
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:42,367
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

112
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,867
You're just wearing that?

113
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:48,967
Umm... for island hopping?

114
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:51,800
Who said we'll go
island hopping?

115
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:57,433
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:06:57,433 --> 00:06:59,000
Are we not?

117
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:08,300
- [JADE] Kiko.
- Oh.

118
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,767
Have you been waiting long?

119
00:07:09,767 --> 00:07:11,033
Ah, not really.

120
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:13,067
Are you ready?

121
00:07:13,067 --> 00:07:15,033
Oh, our amulet!

122
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:17,267
We need to wear it, hurry.

123
00:07:18,067 --> 00:07:20,267
You did a good job
with today's presentation, bud.

124
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:23,133
Well, of course,
I got it from you dad.

125
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:24,500
[ANDY] Let's get going.

126
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,367
[ANDY] What's going on?

127
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,433
Is that Jade?

128
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:35,400
[ANDY] Jade?

129
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,033
Is that why you can't date her?
She has a boyfriend?

130
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,400
[CHUCKLES]

131
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,233
- Let's go.
- Mm-hmm.

132
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:46,067
Wait, how do we get there?

133
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:47,133
Tricycle.

134
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:51,267
- Tricycle?
- Yeah. Let's go.

135
00:07:51,267 --> 00:07:53,000
Okay, okay. Let's go.

136
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,033
Where are they going?

137
00:07:58,033 --> 00:08:00,500
[ANDY] Don't tell me
you'll follow them?

138
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,600
- Dad, c'mon. Let's go.
- What are you doing?

139
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,100
C'mon, just get in.

140
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,000
- Grandpa!
- Oh?

141
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,200
I also left your food
inside the fridge.

142
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,567
Don't forget to take
your medicine too.

143
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:18,733
[BOTONG] What magazine?

144
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:19,833
I'm not reading a magazine.

145
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,867
I said medicine, Grandpa.
The one you need to take.

146
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:23,233
Ah...

147
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:26,067
Remember what
I also told you, okay?

148
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,833
[BOTONG] Yes.

149
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:29,833
Do you even remember
what I told you?

150
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:31,133
[BOTONG] Yeah, I know.
I need to take my medicine.

151
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,300
Not that! The ritual.

152
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:35,067
[BOTONG] What ritual?

153
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:38,300
The ritual that will prevent
Sir Martin's date from happening

154
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,867
with whoever that woman is.

155
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:42,633
My goodness.

156
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:44,667
Okay, fine.

157
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:46,300
- Promise, Grandpa?
- Yes.

158
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,300
Oh!

159
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,100
What is it this time?

160
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:51,800
What?

161
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,267
[AMBIENT MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,667
Oh?

163
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:58,067
Is there a ritual that...

164
00:08:58,067 --> 00:09:00,733
will make me Sir Martin's date?

165
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:02,900
Take this, so you can
have my DNA.

166
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:05,067
Oh my goodness.

167
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:07,300
- Grandpa, please.
- Mhm.

168
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,667
[BOTONG GRUMBLES]

169
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,067
[SARI] Please.

170
00:09:10,067 --> 00:09:11,900
Okay, fine.

171
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,867
- Thanks, Grandpa.
- All right.

172
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:15,900
[SARI] Ah!

173
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:18,700
What is it this time?

174
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:20,733
Buh-bye, Grandpa!
I love you so much.

175
00:09:20,733 --> 00:09:22,700
- Muah!
- Muah!

176
00:09:23,567 --> 00:09:25,200
Bye, Grandpa! Don't forget
to take your medicine, okay?

177
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,967
- Yes. Bye-bye!
- Don't forget it! Buh-bye!

178
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:28,567
- Bye, Grandpa!
- Bye-bye!

179
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:32,600
[AMBIENT MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,300
Do you want to come here?

181
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:37,067
I can fetch you from there.
Then you can stay here for now.

182
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:39,167
Oh, don't bother!

183
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:42,133
I'll just distract you
from your work.

184
00:09:42,133 --> 00:09:43,700
I'm already happy...

185
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:45,633
with you giving me a call.

186
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,233
Okay then.

187
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:49,833
But don't buy groceries
for now, okay?

188
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:51,833
Let's just get whatever
you need delivered there

189
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:53,967
so you won't get too tired.

190
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:55,833
Look at this boy.

191
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:58,133
You wanted me to go
on vacation there earlier,

192
00:09:58,133 --> 00:10:00,133
but you're not letting me
out now

193
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:02,300
because you don't want me
to go to the wet market.

194
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:03,667
What do you want me to do here?

195
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,233
Luna? Is that Luna?

196
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:09,800
- Luna! Luna!
<i> - Grandma, stop.</i>

197
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:12,800
- Luna, is that you?
<i> - Grandma, stop!</i>

198
00:10:13,167 --> 00:10:14,433
Grandma, don't call her.

199
00:10:14,433 --> 00:10:16,900
[GIO'S GRANDMA]<i> She looks
</i>so beautiful! Is that you, Luna?

200
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,767
Hello, Grandma.

201
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:20,767
Yes, this is Luna.

202
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:24,133
[GIO'S GRANDMA]<i> Oh, Luna!
</i>You're still beautiful and sexy.

203
00:10:24,133 --> 00:10:26,000
<i> How are you doing?</i>

204
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,400
I'm doing okay.

205
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,200
How about you?
How's your blood pressure?

206
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:32,233
[GIO'S GRANDMA]
<i> Well, it's still high.</i>

207
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:35,667
But you know, whenever I see
someone pretty, it goes down.

208
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:36,700
Oh my!

209
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,867
You haven't changed.
You still joke a lot.

210
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:41,700
Take care of your health, okay?

211
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:43,300
Getting sick nowadays
is really hard.

212
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:45,933
[GIO'S GRANDMA] Thank you, dear.

213
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:48,300
<i>There's a lot of you who
always remind me about it.</i>

214
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:51,067
Is<i> laing</i> still your favorite?

215
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:54,400
<i> Your laing is
my only favorite.</i>

216
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,833
[GIO'S GRANDMA SQUEALS]
<i> Okay then.</i>

217
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:57,867
<i>I'll have some sent
to you there.</i>

218
00:10:57,867 --> 00:11:01,400
<i>Remind Gio that
I'll send you some, okay?</i>

219
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,000
Okay then, Grandma.

220
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,967
I'll get going to take care
of some stuff.

221
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,767
Oh?

222
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:08,700
Do you work
in the hotel as well?

223
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:10,700
Yes.

224
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,033
Okay then.

225
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:14,867
Bye-bye, Grandma. Take care.

226
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:16,867
- Bye-bye, Grandma.
<i> - You too, dear.</i>

227
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:18,333
Always take care, okay?

228
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:25,300
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,833
<i> Hey!</i>

230
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,233
<i> You're so naughty.</i>

231
00:11:29,233 --> 00:11:31,200
<i> You didn't even tell me
that Luna was there.</i>

232
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:33,900
It doesn't matter, Grandma.

233
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,000
<i> How could it not?</i>

234
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:39,833
<i> She's the only woman
you brought to our house.</i>

235
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,167
<i> I miss you, Grandma!</i>

236
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,333
<i> I miss you so much!</i>

237
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,500
Hmm! There you go again!

238
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,733
There you go again!

239
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:48,333
But when you're ready,
tell me the story, okay?

240
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,100
<i> I love you, my grandson.
I miss you too!</i>

241
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,267
Muah!

242
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:59,233
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:00,967
[SARI] I'm sorry, sir!

244
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:02,300
You know there is a lot
to do at the hotel.

245
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,100
The meeting with Gerard's dad
is already tomorrow.

246
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:06,167
- Then you're late?!
- I'll just extend, sir!

247
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,967
I'll work overtime for free!

248
00:12:08,767 --> 00:12:10,767
- Wait, about Gerard's dad--
- [SHUSHES]

249
00:12:10,767 --> 00:12:11,900
Quiet.

250
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:14,767
Why are you shushing me?

251
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,200
Because this is a personal
meeting.

252
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,767
Sari, promise me you
won't tell anyone else.

253
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,933
[MARTIN SIGHS DEEPLY]

254
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:26,800
Does that mean
you have a date already?

255
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,800
You don't have to
worry about that.

256
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,767
I need the venue. I need food.

257
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:32,433
- And I need flowers.
- You know, sir, you're right!

258
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:33,767
[SHUSHES]

259
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:37,500
You don't have to worry
about the date.

260
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:40,100
You can prove to Mr. Ronald that

261
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,900
you're a good businessman even
if you don't have a date.

262
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:48,000
If he finds out that you're
the perfect example

263
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,233
of a businessman who's TDH!

264
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:51,433
Don't tell me it's tall--

265
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:54,033
T, for thoughtful.

266
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:57,800
You always pay attention
to details and people, sir.

267
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,433
And D, for driven.

268
00:13:00,433 --> 00:13:03,500
You will attack when
needed to, sir!

269
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:06,367
And H, for hands-on.

270
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,433
You're always present
and involved.

271
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:11,867
- That's you, sir! TDH!
- [MARTIN] Raphie!

272
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:13,833
Sir! Sir! Sir!

273
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,933
Edward, are you serious?

274
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:18,333
We even left
the car far away.

275
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,333
Dad, they can't see us.

276
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:22,167
- Hide a bit more.
- [SCOFFS]

277
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,967
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:26,433
Remind me again,
why are we doing this?

279
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:27,600
I'm not even prepared!

280
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,333
Look, I'm wearing leather shoes.

281
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:33,333
I'm sorry, Dad, okay?

282
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:40,000
After the breakfast tomorrow,
we will climb the mountain.

283
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:44,033
The hut you'll sleep in
has been prepared already.

284
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:46,867
You'll be fine sleeping
next to each other, right?

285
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,500
You're a couple anyway.

286
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,867
[EXCLAIMS]

287
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,267
This guy? My boyfriend?

288
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:52,867
H-he's not.

289
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:54,267
[CHUCKLES]

290
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,200
Oh no, I'm sorry.

291
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,300
I thought you were a couple.

292
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,967
What a waste.
You look good together.

293
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:03,333
Ah, her?

294
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,433
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]
She's just my friend.

295
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:08,267
Just so you know,

296
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:10,267
we've been friends
since we were kids.

297
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:13,267
Oh, how adorable.

298
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:20,233
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:14:22,967 --> 00:14:24,100
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

300
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:25,933
[EDWARD] Dad, hide!

301
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,533
Dad!

302
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:31,167
[LAUGHS]

303
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,067
Dad, they might hear us.
Be quiet!

304
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,033
I can't help it, it's funny.

305
00:14:35,967 --> 00:14:37,133
Jade.

306
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,300
What's the matter?

307
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:42,533
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,300
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:47,467
Jade.

310
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:48,600
What's the matter?

311
00:14:50,467 --> 00:14:52,067
Huh?

312
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:54,067
[STUTTERING] Oh, it's nothing.

313
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:56,233
I just thought I had seen...

314
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:57,367
Who?

315
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

316
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:04,667
Never mind.

317
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:06,233
Don't worry about it.

318
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:12,567
Okay, we'll go to the hut then.

319
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:14,633
- It's this way.
- Ah, let's get going.

320
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:24,067
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

321
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:25,567
[EDWARD] You know what, Dad?

322
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:27,067
Leave this to me.

323
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:28,667
I'll handle it myself,
so just go home.

324
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,367
[ANDY] Why should I go home?

325
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:33,133
You brought me here then
you'd tell me to go home?

326
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,300
No, no, no.
I'm staying right here.

327
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,733
I want to see why
you're acting like that.

328
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:40,733
And besides,
this is free entertainment.

329
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:45,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

330
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:46,733
[MARTIN SIGHS] Finally!

331
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:48,733
<i> Pearl said yes?</i>

332
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:51,400
Yes, I'm not
that close with Pearl.

333
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,100
But as soon as I mentioned
your name,

334
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:54,600
she immediately said yes.

335
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:57,567
[EXHALES DEEPLY]
You're such a lifesaver, Trixie.

336
00:15:57,567 --> 00:15:59,333
Do you know that?

337
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,700
Thank you, Trixie.

338
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,233
[TRIXIE] But she said
she had no dress to wear.

339
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,633
You know,
because it's last minute.

340
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:06,233
So, I put in your car

341
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:08,067
the dress that I was going
to lend to her.

342
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,500
I had to do that because,
of course,

343
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,700
I don't know how long
I'll be staying here.

344
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:15,500
[MARTIN SIGHS] I don't know
what I'd do without you.

345
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:18,300
You even accompanied a guest
on a tour, didn't you?

346
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,100
I'm doing this for you, brother.

347
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,700
[MARTIN] I'll make it
up to you, okay?

348
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:27,100
All right. Thanks.
Bye. Love you.

349
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,700
<i>- Take care.
- Love you.</i>

350
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,133
Buh-bye.

351
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:33,567
[PHONE BEEPS]

352
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:34,733
Hey!

353
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,700
You won't wait for me, really?

354
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:40,800
[MARTIN] This is Pearl's number.

355
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,600
Call her and ask what time
she needs to be picked up.

356
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:45,400
Okay.

357
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:47,767
[PHONE CLICKS]

358
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:54,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,300
Pearl Lim.

360
00:16:58,733 --> 00:17:00,067
[CLICKS TONGUE]

361
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:06,300
Huh?

362
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:08,567
She looks like
she's just ahead of me

363
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:10,733
because she's better in English.

364
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:12,700
But we're just equal in looks!

365
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,333
[TRIXIE] Hey!

366
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:17,133
Wait for me!

367
00:17:17,133 --> 00:17:18,100
[COUGHS]

368
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:21,367
Hey, wait for me!

369
00:17:21,367 --> 00:17:22,767
Francheska.

370
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:24,633
Go wait for her.

371
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:25,833
Let's go ahead, Maria.

372
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:29,367
[TRIXIE PANTING]

373
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:30,600
Hey.

374
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,267
What's the matter?

375
00:17:32,267 --> 00:17:33,633
Are you in bad terms?

376
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:36,733
[TRIXIE SCOFFS]

377
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,833
Look at this woman.
I was talking to you.

378
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:41,667
I'll bang your heads
to each other, you'll see.

379
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:44,833
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

380
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,133
Okay.

381
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,300
This way.

382
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,333
[JUSTIN SIGHS]

383
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:58,500
How moody.
We should just be enjoying this.

384
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:01,767
Do you even know
where we're going?

385
00:18:01,767 --> 00:18:03,133
[TRIXIE] Nope.

386
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:04,733
Then why are you all
leading the way?

387
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:06,900
You know, we should
put more of this...

388
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:08,267
[MAN] It's beautiful here.

389
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:09,433
around the hotel.

390
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:17,900
Solenn?

391
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:20,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYS]

392
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,633
Solenn.

393
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:23,700
- Solenn!
- Cha-Chase?

394
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:24,700
Oh my god!

395
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,533
[CHUCKLES] Wow!

396
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:27,800
I missed you!

397
00:18:28,367 --> 00:18:29,533
I can't believe it.

398
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:31,300
We haven't seen
each other in a long time.

399
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,400
How have you been?

400
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:34,600
It's been what?

401
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:36,367
It's been a few years, right?

402
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:38,500
[LUNA] What are you doing here?

403
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,700
[CHASE] Well...

404
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:43,367
You haven't come back
in Manila for a long time.

405
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:45,733
Wait a second, when did
you last come to the bar?

406
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:48,200
It's been a while.

407
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,200
How long has it been?

408
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,600
Wow, you know what?

409
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,600
I used to always ask Peter
where you were.

410
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:55,333
You didn't even reply to me.

411
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:57,333
All the while,
you were just here.

412
00:18:57,767 --> 00:19:01,367
You know, Peter and I still
hang out to this day.

413
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:03,767
There's this new bar in QC.

414
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,767
You know, we're still the same.

415
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:07,767
You know how that man is.

416
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:09,600
Do you guys still talk?

417
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

418
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:13,933
Reservation! Do you have
a reservation already?

419
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:17,533
- Hey, is there a "Chase" there?
- Here, here!

420
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:19,633
Why don't you seem to have
any trust in me?

421
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:23,533
You know, there's no vacancy
at my friends' hotel anymore.

422
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:25,433
That's why I came here instead.

423
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:28,267
If only I had known
you were working here,

424
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,300
we would've all
booked here instead.

425
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:33,633
You know, I missed you
and Peter so much.

426
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:34,800
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

427
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,700
[CHASE] Our night-out parties
were wild, weren't they?

428
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:39,533
I missed our dance moves
like this one.

429
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,533
Those parties were so fun!

430
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:43,533
Didn't you even miss that?

431
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:45,367
It's good to see you, Chase.

432
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:46,733
That quickly?

433
00:19:47,367 --> 00:19:48,767
I missed you!

434
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:50,933
You know, I missed you so much.

435
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:52,767
I hope we could party
together again.

436
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,933
Later.

437
00:19:53,933 --> 00:19:55,300
Let's see each other, okay?

438
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,667
Yes, okay.

439
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:59,933
Let's party later, okay?

440
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

441
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,000
- Please sign here, sir.
- Which one?

442
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,267
[DOOR OPENS]

443
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,800
[DOOR THUDS]

444
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:19,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

445
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:26,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

446
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:34,767
<i> With so many hotels out there,</i>

447
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,533
<i> why is Peter's friend here?</i>

448
00:20:37,533 --> 00:20:44,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

449
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:53,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

450
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,000
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

451
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,800
Sir, we're closed today.

452
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,833
Ma'am, please.
I just need to ask something.

453
00:21:01,467 --> 00:21:02,567
We're closed, sir.

454
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:03,900
- [KNOCKING CONTINUES]
- Please, ma'am.

455
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:06,233
Can you open the door?

456
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,467
[KEYS CLICKING]

457
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,000
[DOOR LOCK CLICKS]

458
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:16,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

459
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:19,433
Ma'am, uh...
I just want to know

460
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:22,333
who sent the package
to Michael Fernandez

461
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,200
during Holy Week.

462
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,533
Uh, go ahead,
just take it to storage.

463
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:27,867
Okay, ma'am.

464
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:33,200
But Mr. Almazan,
the sender is confidential

465
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,267
unless the receiver
is the one asking.

466
00:21:35,267 --> 00:21:42,233
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

467
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:47,233
Uh, ma'am,
you don't need to print it.

468
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:50,100
Just type it here
on my phone.

469
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,167
So it can't be traced
back to you.

470
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:05,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

471
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:12,867
[KEYBOARD CLINKING]

472
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:21,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

473
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:40,033
"Vito Arsenia #107 Victor
Drive, Puerto Felicia"

474
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:47,567
Thank you.

475
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:56,500
- [EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CROW CAWING]

476
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:04,233
[CROW CAWING]

477
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:13,333
[MAN] Who are you?

478
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:16,200
Vito Arsenia?

479
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:20,167
Leon Almazan.

480
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:21,867
Are you Vito?

481
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,000
What do you need?

482
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:26,067
You sent documents
to Michael Fernandez

483
00:23:26,067 --> 00:23:27,500
before he died.

484
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:28,567
Do you remember?

485
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:32,067
You're Federico Almazan's son?

486
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,233
Come in.

487
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:44,967
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

488
00:23:48,067 --> 00:23:49,633
Is this some kind of sun dance?

489
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:51,933
<i>We dance up here and
our bad luck disappears?</i>

490
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:53,033
<i> That's what he said.</i>

491
00:23:53,033 --> 00:23:55,400
<i>I just really can't leave Jade
with that guy.</i>

492
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,400
<i>Every time they're together,
something bad happens.</i>

493
00:23:57,433 --> 00:23:59,033
<i> Well, Pearl's not coming.</i>

494
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:00,533
<i> So I need a new date.</i>

495
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:02,200
<i>Just admit it, you want
you guys to be the only ones</i>

496
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,167
<i>with the upper hand
here in the hotel!</i>

497
00:24:03,167 --> 00:24:05,967
[SCOFFS]<i>
</i>All you do is keep attacking.

498
00:24:05,967 --> 00:24:08,400
<i>Paying off the bank loan
is urgent!</i>

499
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,433
<i>We are going to invest
in Hotel 88.</i>

500
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:12,000
<i> Invest?</i>

501
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,067
<i> Partner?</i>

502
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:14,667
<i> Leon, he's so quiet, right?</i>

503
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:16,267
<i> But from what I can see,</i>

504
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:18,000
<i>he's the one
with the most secrets.</i>

505
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:19,233
<i>What do you have to do
with Sandro?</i>

506
00:24:19,233 --> 00:24:22,533
<i>Don't you ever mention
that name in this house again!</i>

507
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,300
<i> You!</i>

508
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:26,167
There's a shadow following you.

509
00:24:26,167 --> 00:24:28,200
<i>There are dangers
waiting for you.</i>

510
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:30,033
[BLOW LANDS]

